                     BEVINGTON, Henry; 





                     WELLINGS, Charles (45, agent); 





                     MIL
LINGTON, Herbert (26, jobmaster); and 





                     CLARKE. Charles (24, steward)


                     , were now indicted for forging and uttering, knowing the same to be forged, an order for the payment of ₤ 1, 500, with intent to defraud.

Sentence, 



                     Five years' penal servitude; 


                     recommended for expulsion under the Aliens Act.

